```julia
function clean_column(col::AbstractString)
    return lowercase(strip(col)) |> replace(' ', '_') |> replace('-', '_')
end
```

This function uses the `lowercase`, `strip`, `replace` functions to achieve the desired result. It first lowers the case of the string using `lowercase`, then strips any leading or trailing whitespaces with `strip`. Finally, it replaces both spaces and hyphens with underscores using `replace`. The pipeline operator (`|>`) is used to chain these operations together.
